00:00:02.540 --> 00:00:05.550
VO:
Everyone wants a beautiful, healthy smile.

00:00:05.550 --> 00:00:09.460
Your decision to wear braces is proof that
your smile really matters to you.

00:00:09.460 --> 00:00:13.370
Here is some important information to help
you achieve the bright new smile you’ve

00:00:13.370 --> 00:00:15.250
always wanted, from Crest Oral-B.

00:00:15.250 --> 00:00:16.250
Super:
Crest Oral-B

00:00:16.250 --> 00:00:17.250
POOR

00:00:17.250 --> 00:00:18.900
VO:
While you’re wearing braces, it’s extra

00:00:18.900 --> 00:00:21.970
important to take good care of your teeth
and gums.

00:00:21.970 --> 00:00:26.640
Brackets and bands can trap pieces of food
that promote bacterial growth and tooth decay.

00:00:26.640 --> 00:00:29.430
If you don’t take care of your teeth, they
can weaken and discolor.

00:00:29.430 --> 00:00:33.810
It’s important that you keep your mouth,
teeth, and braces clean at all times.

00:00:33.810 --> 00:00:34.810
Super:
EXCELLENT

00:00:34.810 --> 00:00:36.780
VO:
This dental office is dedicated to helping

00:00:36.780 --> 00:00:38.430
you get the best results possible.

00:00:38.430 --> 00:00:41.650
That’s why we’ve adopted the ortho essentials
program.

00:00:41.650 --> 00:00:42.650
Super:
Ortho essentials

00:00:42.650 --> 00:00:43.650
Wire your world

00:00:43.650 --> 00:00:45.180
VO:
If you follow this program using the Pro Health

00:00:45.180 --> 00:00:50.760
system, and other great Crest Oral-B products,
you can achieve excellent results for a beautiful,

00:00:50.760 --> 00:00:51.760
healthy smile.

00:00:51.760 --> 00:00:52.760
Super:
PRO-HEALTH SYSTEM

00:00:52.760 --> 00:00:54.310
VO:
The ortho essentials products are designed

00:00:54.310 --> 00:00:57.040
to work together to deliver great results.

00:00:57.040 --> 00:01:02.040
Twice daily use of the electric toothbrush
loosens and sweeps away plaque, a sticky germ

00:01:02.040 --> 00:01:06.630
containing substance that builds up on your
teeth and gums and may cause gum disease.

00:01:06.630 --> 00:01:11.200
And the use of Crest Pro Health toothpaste
and rinse helps prevent plaque regrowth all

00:01:11.200 --> 00:01:12.480
day and all night.

00:01:12.480 --> 00:01:17.640
With plaque at the root of most oral health
issues for people wearing braces, we recommend

00:01:17.640 --> 00:01:22.030
regular use of this system while in orthodontic
treatment, to protect the commitment you are

00:01:22.030 --> 00:01:23.030
making to your smile.

00:01:23.030 --> 00:01:24.030
SUPER:
electric brushing : )

00:01:24.030 --> 00:01:25.780
VO:
Now, let’s review how to brush and floss

00:01:25.780 --> 00:01:27.310
while wearing braces.

00:01:27.310 --> 00:01:30.740
Did you know that brushing with a regular
manual toothbrush can leave a great deal of

00:01:30.740 --> 00:01:31.740
plaque behind?

00:01:31.740 --> 00:01:32.740
Super:
Brushing with manual toothbrush can leave

00:01:32.740 --> 00:01:33.740
a great deal of plaque behind

00:01:33.740 --> 00:01:34.740
VO:
You can do a better job of removing plaque

00:01:34.740 --> 00:01:36.430
and reducing gingivitis by using an Oral-B
electric brush.

00:01:36.430 --> 00:01:38.090
Super:
Oral-B Electric Brushes do a better job or

00:01:38.090 --> 00:01:39.090
removing plaque and reducing gingivitis.

00:01:39.090 --> 00:01:40.530
VO:
The Oral-B electric brush is lightweight,

00:01:40.530 --> 00:01:43.290
so you can hold it with a light fingertip
grip.

00:01:43.290 --> 00:01:44.290
Super:
Hold brush parallel to floor

00:01:44.290 --> 00:01:45.560
VO:
Hold it parallel to the floor, against the

00:01:45.560 --> 00:01:46.950
side of your teeth.

00:01:46.950 --> 00:01:51.150
Guide the brush head slowly from tooth to
tooth, following the natural curve of your

00:01:51.150 --> 00:01:52.150
teeth and gums.

00:01:52.150 --> 00:01:53.150
Super:
No need to push hard or scrub

00:01:53.150 --> 00:01:55.200
VO:
You don’t have to press hard or scrub.

00:01:55.200 --> 00:01:57.680
Simply let the brush do all the work for you.

00:01:57.680 --> 00:01:58.680
Super:
Hold the brush on each tooth for a few seconds

00:01:58.680 --> 00:01:59.680
before moving on

00:01:59.680 --> 00:02:00.680
VO:
Hold the brush in place on each tooth for

00:02:00.680 --> 00:02:03.189
a few seconds before moving on to the next
tooth.

00:02:03.189 --> 00:02:06.490
Clean all of your teeth one by one, and don’t
forget to reach all areas.

00:02:06.490 --> 00:02:07.490
Super:
Clean insides, clean outsides, clean top chewing

00:02:07.490 --> 00:02:08.490
surfaces, clean behind back molars
Clean brackets by angling the brush head against

00:02:08.490 --> 00:02:09.490
them
Clean between brackets and gums and under

00:02:09.490 --> 00:02:10.490
wires

00:02:10.490 --> 00:02:11.490
VO:
The insides, outsides, the chewing surfaces,

00:02:11.490 --> 00:02:13.370
and even at the back of your mouth, behind
your back molars.

00:02:13.370 --> 00:02:17.319
Be sure to clean the brackets thoroughly by
angling the brush head against them.

00:02:17.319 --> 00:02:21.299
Make sure the electric brush cleans between
the brackets and your gums, and under the

00:02:21.299 --> 00:02:23.390
orthodontic wires.

00:02:23.390 --> 00:02:27.540
Remember to replace your brush head every
3 months, as the efficiency of the brush decreases

00:02:27.540 --> 00:02:28.540
with longer usage.

00:02:28.540 --> 00:02:29.540
Super:
Studies show that a toothbrush used for 3

00:02:29.540 --> 00:02:30.540
months removed less plaque than a new toothbrush
and its efficiency decreased with longer usage

00:02:30.540 --> 00:02:31.540
VO:
To learn more, see the instructions that came

00:02:31.540 --> 00:02:33.470
with your Oral-B electric brush.

00:02:33.470 --> 00:02:35.309
Super:
Flossing : )

00:02:35.309 --> 00:02:38.480
VO:
While wearing braces, it’s even more critical

00:02:38.480 --> 00:02:40.470
to floss regularly.

00:02:40.470 --> 00:02:45.450
Pieces of food lodge between teeth and around
the braces, and can get trapped causing tooth

00:02:45.450 --> 00:02:46.650
decay.

00:02:46.650 --> 00:02:48.919
Flossing is also effective at removing plaque.

00:02:48.919 --> 00:02:54.050
Both Oral-B Superfloss, and Crest Glide Threader
floss make flossing with braces easy,

00:02:54.050 --> 00:02:55.050
Super:
Crest Glide Threader floss has a stiff end

00:02:55.050 --> 00:02:56.050
for threading

00:02:56.050 --> 00:02:57.050
VO:
because the stiff end allows you to thread

00:02:57.050 --> 00:02:59.069
the floss between your brackets.

00:02:59.069 --> 00:03:01.120
You simply insert the threader under the wire,

00:03:01.120 --> 00:03:03.799
Super:
Insert the threader between two teeth and

00:03:03.799 --> 00:03:04.799
push floss halfway through

00:03:04.799 --> 00:03:05.799
VO:
over the space between two teeth, push the

00:03:05.799 --> 00:03:08.599
floss through halfway, and then grasp both
ends of the floss with your fingers.

00:03:08.599 --> 00:03:12.819
Gently work the floss back and forth between
each tooth a few times.

00:03:12.819 --> 00:03:17.189
When you reach the gum line, curve the floss
into a “c” shape, following the line of

00:03:17.189 --> 00:03:18.189
the tooth
Super:

00:03:18.189 --> 00:03:19.189
Make sure to floss down below the gum line

00:03:19.189 --> 00:03:20.769
VO:
making sure you floss down below the gum line.

00:03:20.769 --> 00:03:24.689
To move on to the next tooth, pull the floss
out and re thread it out under the next wire.

00:03:24.689 --> 00:03:25.689
Super:
Do not pull on the floss too fast or you may

00:03:25.689 --> 00:03:26.689
cause a bracket to come loose

00:03:26.689 --> 00:03:27.689
VO:
Be careful not to pull on the floss too fast,

00:03:27.689 --> 00:03:31.809
or you might cause a bracket to come loose
or shred the floss on the braces.

00:03:31.809 --> 00:03:33.419
Continue this process on each tooth

00:03:33.419 --> 00:03:34.419
Super:
Remember to do the back of your mouth

00:03:34.419 --> 00:03:36.309
VO:
remembering to do the very back of your mouth.

00:03:36.309 --> 00:03:40.390
Your gums may bleed for the first week, until
the plaque layer is broken up.

00:03:40.390 --> 00:03:42.659
Bacteria are removed, and your gums heal.

00:03:42.659 --> 00:03:44.260
This is normal, and nothing to worry about.

00:03:44.260 --> 00:03:45.260
Super:
Flossing daily increases your chance to keep

00:03:45.260 --> 00:03:46.260
your teeth for a lifetime

00:03:46.260 --> 00:03:47.260
VO:
If you floss every day, you increase your

00:03:47.260 --> 00:03:49.099
chance of keeping your teeth for a lifetime.

